Interface OneQueryCollectStep<R extends org.jooq.Record>

All Known Subinterfaces:

All Known Implementing Classes:
OneQuery
public interface OneQueryCollectStep<R extends org.jooq.Record>
Interface casts the result to a specific collection, which are terminal methods

In version 0.0.1, only list casting is available

  • Method Details

    • toList

      @NotNull <C> @NotNull List<C> toList(Class<C> clazz)
      The method takes a class to which all objects in the response must be cast. If you need to welcome an entity to the generated jooq class, you need to use the classes from the pojos package.

    • toList

      @NotNull <C> @NotNull List<C> toList(org.jooq.RecordMapper<R,C> mapper)
      The method accepts an entity mapper with Record as a parameter.

      Example mapper: 

      
     record2 -> {
        String[] array = new String[2];
        array[0] = record2.value1();
        array[1] = record2.value2();
        return array;
     }
